---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Strategy Library — under revision"
  description="The n0brains Strategy Library is temporarily offline while we rebuild it on properly forward-tested results. The signal feed and /proof are unaffected."
>
  <section class="docs-page">
    <h1>Strategy Library</h1>
    <p class="docs-subtitle">Temporarily offline &middot; under revision</p>

    <div class="card legal-card">
      <h2>This page is being rebuilt.</h2>
      <p>
        We've taken the reference strategy configurations down. The exit rules we
        had published (fixed take-profit / stop-loss / horizon per signal type)
        were derived from a historical backtest that did not hold up under live
        forward-testing — most positions closed on the time horizon rather than at
        their target, so the configurations were not a fair representation of how
        the signals actually perform.
      </p>
      <p>
        Rather than leave up numbers we no longer stand behind, we're rebuilding
        this library from <strong>live, forward-tested results only</strong>. We'll
        republish a configuration here when — and only when — it has proven itself
        on real, going-forward signals.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>What's unaffected</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>The <a href="/docs">signal API</a> and live WebSocket feed — fully operational.</li>
        <li>Our live, ongoing performance numbers at <a href="/proof">/proof</a> — these are the real forward-test, untouched.</li>
        <li>Per-signal-type forward returns (1h / 4h / 24h) continue to be recorded.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Questions or want to be notified when the library returns?
        <a href="mailto:support@n0brains.com">Email support</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-card {
    border-left: 3px solid #b13838;
    background: rgba(177, 56, 56, 0.06);
  }
  .legal-card h2 { color: #ef4444; }
  .legal-card strong { color: var(--text-heading); }
</style>
